Lit is an app to teach reading to adults on smartphones and in web browsers. One billion people worldwide cannot read. Technology now gives people the means to learn anywhere, anytime. It's in their pockets.

Code is Javascript, HTML, CSS. PhoneGap is used to allow the code to run on mobile devices. Android is currently the primary goal since these devices are the most wide-spread and affordable.

Pop on over to the website to discuss and get involved. There are lots of interesting tasks beyond coding.



